Step 1: Factor out the common term $(1-2+3-4+5-6+7)$ from both the numerator and denominator.

$$\begin{align*}
\frac{2-4+6-8+10-12+14}{3-6+9-12+15-18+21} &= \frac{2(1-2+3-4+5-6+7)}{3(1-2+3-4+5-6+7)}
\end{align*}$$

Step 2: Cancel out the common factor $(1-2+3-4+5-6+7)$ from both the numerator and denominator.

$$\begin{align*}
